{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"50a6cb57-8267-42e4-b897-b05a06be90d7","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2 / .NET 9.0**, so you can use the modern patterns:\n\n### Recommended approach\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous init here\n    }\n\n    // Async init via [TestInitialize]\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // await async setup work\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Hello from test\");\n        Assert.IsTrue(true);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via constructor (modern). The old `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` static property pattern still works but constructor injection is preferred in v3+.\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize] public async Task ...`. Constructors can't be async, so this is the only option for awaitable setup.\n- **Cleanup** — similarly, `[TestCleanup]` supports `async Task`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"71f58abf-3242-40d0-bd97-28cc77407748","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. Let me provide the modern MSTest guidance.\n\nIn MSTest v3+, the recommended approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection (`TestContext` as a constructor parameter) rather than the legacy static property pattern.\n2. **Synchronous init**: Use the constructor or `[TestInitialize]` method.\n3. **Asynchronous init**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with `async Task` return type (supported in MSTest v2+).\n\nLet me give a concise, accurate answer.","outputTokens":474,"requestId":"1BC5:1BD824:D17773:ED1B21:6A03D785"},"id":"57da8ce5-a5da-4805-9f92-0816777f2bb2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:44:48.419Z","parentId":"2f62d8c1-81bf-4c27-aa82-ab451a2bd3ff"}
